claim.claim-text:
8. The method of claim 7, wherein the forming of the insulating layer, the insulating guard ring, and the at least one conductive guard ring comprises:
forming a lower interlayer dielectric layer over the semiconductor substrate;
forming a lower insulating guard ring surrounding at least a portion of the main chip region, the lower insulating guard ring being formed in the lower interlayer dielectric layer;
forming at least one lower conductive guard ring surrounding at least a portion of the main chip region, the at least one lower conductive guard ring being formed in the lower interlayer dielectric layer;
forming an upper interlayer dielectric layer over the lower interlayer dielectric layer, the lower insulating guard ring, and the at least one lower conductive guard ring;
forming an upper insulating guard ring that penetrates the upper interlayer dielectric layer to contact the lower insulating guard ring; and
forming at least one upper conductive guard ring that penetrates the upper interlayer dielectric layer to contact the at least one lower conductive guard ring.
